		<band height="105">
			<staticText>
				<reportElement positionType="Float" x="25" y="0" width="545" height="105" uuid="d6f3ffec-fa89-4da4-8e00-95d2c45b4291"/>
				<textElement textAlignment="Justified" verticalAlignment="Middle" markup="html">
					<font size="12" pdfFontName="net/sf/jasperreports/fonts/dejavu/DejaVuSerif-Italic.ttf" isPdfEmbedded="true"/>
				</textElement>
				<text><![CDATA[It should be considered that under some disease conditions, such as tumours, molecular features may not be present homogeneously in the tissue sample. Therefore, it is important that the part of actual tissue sample used for molecular analysis is evaluated by a medically qualified pathologist. In this context it should be documented which aspect of a disease is actually reflected in the tissue sample used for molecular analysis.]]></text>
			</staticText>
		</band>
